unveil
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:remove the cover from a Maori headstone in a ceremony a certain time after the burial.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:see also unveiling n.
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1984 citation shows a deceased person, as well as their gravestone, can be 'unveiled'
